article.headline: East Tenn. St. 88, Jacksonville 73
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Tim Smith scored 27 points, had eight assists and seven steals to lead East Tennessee State to an 88-73 win over Jacksonville Friday, while stretching the nation's longest current losing streak to 18 consecutive games. Smith connected on 10-of-18 shots and added six free throws as he hiked his career point total to 2,165. Smith's seven steals in the game hiked his nation-leading total to 75 this year. Smith keyed a 17-2 run over a four-minute stretch in the first half when the Buccaneers (13-8, 10-4) broke a 17-17 and took a 34-19 lead with seven minutes left in the first half. The Bucs connected on eight of 10 shots during the spurt with Smith scoring seven points and Dillion Sneed coming off the bench to add six. After holding a 47-36 lead at the half, East Tennessee State scored the first ten points of the second half. They took their biggest lead of the night at 74-44 with 11:45 left in the game. Aubrey Conerly and Ljubisa Vrcelj each scored 13 points for Jacksonville (1-20, 1-13) which has not won since beating city rival North Florida on December 2.
